<TITLE> Police arrest 3 Dhaka College students </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 19 (bdnews24.com)  The police arrested three Dhaka College students as they clashed with law enforcers in the wake of violence that halted traffic on Mirpur Road Saturday. Angry students briefly blocked traffic on the busy road after a passenger bus rammed into a Dhaka College bus from behind. The students became involved in a scuffle with the bus driver and conductor, spreading violence in the area. The police fired rubber bullets to bring the situation under control. One student alleged that traffic police sergeant Bashirul Haque was on the scene when the bus driver and conductor beat a number of students. The officer in charge of New Market Police Station confirmed the news of the arrests. bdn
